(29, 2, '2010-09-13 14:27:21', '2010-09-13 13:27:21', 'Withens Clough Reservoir is like a forgotten land- down on the edge of the water, the stumps of old drowned trees that I assume are usually under the waterline but for the lack of rainfall.\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-52" href="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/withens-clough-reservoir/withens-clough-beach/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-52" title="Withens Clough beach" src="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/files/2010/09/Withens-Clough-beach-640x426.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="426" /></a>\r\n\r\nthe mud is gorgeous - black , smooth, a bit claggy so good to model with. Its like a cross between clay &amp; peat.So I dug some up with a stone, to make sculpture back at home - out of the relentless heavy drizzle and whipping rain- Frankie, my lurcher, offered advice-\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-53" href="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/withens-clough-reservoir/digging-at-withens-clough/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-53" title="Digging at Withens Clough" src="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/files/2010/09/digging-at-withens-clough-640x426.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="426" /></a>', 'Withens Clough Reservoir', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'withens-clough-reservoir', '', '', '2010-09-21 12:29:01', '2010-09-21 12:29:01', '', 0, 'http://sallybarker.local/?p=29', 0, 'post', '', 1),
